\left(\frac{a}{n}\right) =\left(\frac{b}{n}\right)
a \equiv b\pmod n
\left(\frac{0}{n}\right)=0
\left(\frac{n}{n}\right)=0
\left(\frac{ab}{n}\right) =\left(\frac{a}{n}\right) \left(\frac{b}{n}\right)
\left(\frac{-1}{n}\right)\neq-1
n \equiv 3 \pmod 4
 \left(\frac{n-b}{n}\right)= \left(\frac{-b}{n}\right)= \left(\frac{-1}{n}\right) \left(\frac{b}{n}\right)\neq -\left(\frac{b}{n}\right)= 0-\left(\frac{b}{n}\right)= \left(\frac{n}{n}\right)- \left(\frac{b}{n}\right) 
